0\n| Title           = The Ape\n| WrittenBy       = Ben Bocquelet, Jon Foster, James Lamont, and Mic Graves\n| Aux2            = Chuck Klein and Rob Latimer\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|1|16}}\n| Viewers         = 1.79<ref>{{cite report |title=Broadcast TV Ratings: Cartoon Network (January 30\u2013February 5, 2012) |publisher=[[Nielsen Media Research]] |date=February 11, 2012}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Miss Simian cozies up to Gumball and his family in order to win an award. \n| LineColor       = 5ec5c4\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Amazing World of Gumball (season 1)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 31\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 31\n| Title           = The Car\n| WrittenBy       = Ben Bocquelet, Jon Foster, James Lamont, and Mic Graves\n| Aux2            = Ben Marsaud\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|2|7}}\n| Viewers         = 1.68<ref>{{cite report |title=Broadcast TV Ratings: Cartoon Network (February 6\u201312, 2012) |publisher=[[Nielsen Media Research]] |date=February 18, 2012}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Gumball and Darwin are eager enough to do numerous chores at Mr. Robinson's house, until they accidentally destroy his car.\n| LineColor       = 5ec5c4\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Amazing World of Gumball (season 1)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 32\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 32\n| Title           = The Curse\n| WrittenBy       = Ben Bocquelet, Jon Foster, James Lamont, and Mic Graves\n| Aux2            = Rob Latimer and George Gendi\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2012|2|14}}\n| Viewers         = 1.91<ref>{{cite report |title=Broadcast TV Ratings: Cartoon Network (February 13\u201319, 2012) |publisher=[[Nielsen Media Research]] |date=February 23, 2012}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Gumball's good day turns from bad to worse throughout his school day, much to the point where he believes he is cursed.\nSongs: Today\u2019s Gonna Be A Wonderful Day!, When Life Hands You Lemons\n| LineColor       = 5ec5c4\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Amazing World of Gumball (season 1)\n